deepseek.analysis: 原积分 $\int \frac{\sin x}{\cos^2 x} dx = \int \frac{1}{\cos^2 x} \sin x dx$。令 $u = \cos x$，则 $du = -\sin x dx$，即 $\sin x dx = -du$。代入得 $\int \frac{1}{u^2} (-du) = -\int u^{-2} du = -\frac{u^{-1}}{-1} + C = \frac{1}{u} + C = \frac{1}{\cos x} + C = \sec x + C$。
